An in-depth study published in 2006 shows that 80.6% of Vietnamese women believe a man and his wife have the right to decide on having an abortion or giving a birth to a child2 (Tuong, The Role of Contraception and Abortion in Vietnam: Social Change in Modern Livelihood, 2006).
2 For the full report http://www.popcouncil.org/documents/WPS_73_Tuong_Am_Zen_2006.pdf
Above: An advertisement on Abortion Safety and Post Abortion Care that can be found in the corridors of ObGYN clinic on the 1st floor of Cho Ray Hospital. This poster was developed by CHO RAY Savings and Credit Union, which has been functioning for over 25 years.
Left: A poster inside the facility at the 5th floor of Great ObGYN center “Cho Ray Palace”. In 2017 approximately 40,066 patients were treated by the center. The center offers contraception, pregnancy counseling, guardianship, physical examination and also performs surgical, medical and surgical abortions.
In 1995, Vietnam reported 616,017 induced abortions with the rate per 1000 women aged 15-44 being 163.0, according to the world health report for 1996 (Abortion – information sheet Gynecologic/Abdominal Procedures/Obstetrics/Gynecology services and resources part of The
